Package: maxdiff
Title: Hierarchical Bayesian MaxDiff (Best-Worst Scaling) Analysis
Version: 0.0.1
Date: 2026-06-18
Authors@R: person("Dan", "Yavorsky", email = "dyavorsky@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Design, fit, and visualize MaxDiff (best-worst scaling) studies
    using a hierarchical Bayesian multinomial logit model. The HB MNL Gibbs
    sampler is self-contained — adapted from Peter Rossi's bayesm package
    (Rossi, Allenby, and McCulloch, 2024) with an extension to support
    ragged choice sets. Ragged choice sets enable the exact best-then-worst
    joint likelihood: K alternatives for the best pick, K-1 for the worst
    (excluding the best item). See Rossi, Allenby, and McCulloch (2024,
    ISBN:978-1-118-97218-3) for the statistical foundation.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
